    "description": "This is a persistent-exposure strategy built around a small universe of highly liquid, large-cap stocks, where large-cap liquid stocks are ranked relative to a volatility reference, establishing a core long basket complemented by a smaller, asymmetrical short sleeve that primarily serves as a stabilizer rather than a return engine. During the trading day, the strategy repeatedly corrects for drift by reasserting target position sizes whenever execution effects, risk controls, or price movement p",
    "description_full": "This is a persistent-exposure strategy built around a small universe of highly liquid, large-cap stocks, where large-cap liquid stocks are ranked relative to a volatility reference, establishing a core long basket complemented by a smaller, asymmetrical short sleeve that primarily serves as a stabilizer rather than a return engine. During the trading day, the strategy repeatedly corrects for drift by reasserting target position sizes whenever execution effects, risk controls, or price movement pull allocations off-course. This “snap-back” behavior keeps capital anchored in the most resilient large-cap trends, minimizes unintended time out of the market, and compresses the distribution of outcomes, producing unusually consistent long-horizon performance in regimes where liquidity and trend persistence matter.",
